Categorize numerical columns¶

Create Custom Function¶

In [179]:
def categorize(x,a):
  # x : row instance of a pandas dataframe;
  # a : type=ndArrayObject, categorical segments to categorize x
  time_app = a
  result=''
  for index,i in enumerate(time_app):
    if x>time_app[index]:
      if index<=len(time_app):
        if time_app[index]!=time_app[-1]:
          if x<time_app[index+1]:
            result = f'''{time_app[index]}  to  {time_app[index+1]}'''
        else:
          result = f''' {time_app[index-1]}  to  {time_app[-1]} '''
  return result

Linear Regression Model¶

Model¶

In [184]:
df2 = df[['Avg. Session Length', 'Time on App','Time on Website', 'Length of Membership', 'Yearly Amount Spent']]
x = df2.drop('Yearly Amount Spent',axis=1)
y= df2['Yearly Amount Spent']
X_train,X_test,Y_train,Y_test = train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.8,random_state=None)
sc = StandardScaler()
X_train  = sc.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test  = sc.fit_transform(X_test)
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X_train,Y_train)
pred = model.predict(X_test)

In [185]:
Y_test.index = range(len(Y_test))
result = pd.concat([Y_test,pd.DataFrame(pred)[0]],axis=1)

result=result.rename(columns={'Yearly Amount Spent': 'Original',0:'Prediction'}).reset_index()
result=result.melt(id_vars=['index'],value_vars=['Original','Prediction'])

a = np.arange(-3,6,3)

a = np.arange(300,1100,200)
df_pred['Predicted_spent']= df_pred['prediction'].apply(lambda x: categorize(x,a))
a = np.arange(300,1100,200)
df_pred['Original_spent']= df_pred['Yearly Amount Spent'].apply(lambda x: categorize(x,a))
